Install it like this:

$ rm -rf .vim/ .vimrc .gvimrc
$ cd ~
$ git clone [--recursive] git://github.com/Osse/Vim-config.git .vim

The configuration files .vimrc and .gvimrc are located inside the .vim directory to making using the repo easier. To use them as your regular config files for Vim, set up links to them like this:

$ cd ~
$ ln -s .vim/vimrc .vimrgc
$ ln -s .vim/gvimrc .gvimrc

If '--recursive' was left out, install Vundle 'manually':

$ git submodule update --init

After that, run :BundleInstall from within Vim. This makes Vundle automatically install all the plugins listed in vimrc as 'bundles.'
